00:31:45.111 --> 00:31:47.661
about how we can create
excellent versions of those.

00:31:50.291 --> 00:31:53.871
The first thing to think
about with spreadsheets is index sheets,

00:31:53.877 --> 00:31:55.550
and they are really important.

00:31:57.351 --> 00:31:59.120
If you have several sheets
in your workbook,

00:31:59.120 --> 00:32:01.731
it's really helpful
to provide an index sheet

00:32:02.290 --> 00:32:03.290
at the beginning.

00:32:03.680 --> 00:32:05.890
That should tell the user
what the workbook is about

00:32:05.890 --> 00:32:09.278
and provide a contents list,
which is hyperlinked to each sheet.

00:32:09.830 --> 00:32:12.891
It might be quite obvious
why that's important and hopefully it is.

00:32:12.891 --> 00:32:15.771
It's so that users can access
the information clearly,

00:32:16.391 --> 00:32:19.791
they know what that spreadsheet is about,
and they can really delve into details

00:32:19.791 --> 00:32:20.791
straight away.

00:32:22.968 --> 00:32:27.801
Cell A1 is such an important cell
but often is not thought about too much.

00:32:28.760 --> 00:32:30.260
It should never be left blank.

00:32:30.831 --> 00:32:32.361
There are different ways
you can use it though

00:32:32.361 --> 00:32:34.071
and this is where it gets interesting.

00:32:34.071 --> 00:32:35.321
That's why on this slide,

00:32:35.481 --> 00:32:39.831
