00:39:54.291 --> 00:39:56.349
Thank you for sharing that.

00:39:56.350 --> 00:39:59.160
The next question we have is from,

00:40:01.980 --> 00:40:03.759
I'm not going to try
to pronounce this.

00:40:03.760 --> 00:40:10.240
I use PAC 2024 for checking PDFs
and the Acrobat built-in functions.

00:40:10.600 --> 00:40:14.329
Can you recommend
other tools that we could use?

00:40:14.980 --> 00:40:17.359
Samantha: Kind of similar question,
I guess, to the last one in a way.

00:40:17.360 --> 00:40:20.349
There's another free tool
called PAVE, which you can use.

00:40:20.350 --> 00:40:23.919
That's mostly up for files
that are less than five megabytes.

00:40:23.920 --> 00:40:26.709
It depends on the size
of your file on that one.

00:40:26.710 --> 00:40:28.359
But there are also lots
of paid-for tools.

00:40:28.360 --> 00:40:29.819
I don't use any of them myself,

00:40:29.820 --> 00:40:31.929
so I can't recommend
one or the other.

00:40:31.930 --> 00:40:36.153
But there are lots of names
like CommonLit PDF, Axes 4, Equidox.

00:40:36.154 --> 00:40:38.679
These are all examples
